#IdentificaciÃ³n de enlaces prioritarios

library(sf)
library(terra)     # para leer el raster de resistencia (rast)
library(raster)    # para gdistance
library(gdistance)
library(dplyr)
library(purrr)

# --------------------------
# 0) ParÃ¡metros y datos base
# --------------------------
umbral_area_m2 <- 15000000      # 40.97 kmÂ²

resistance_matrix <- raster(resistencia)      # objeto RasterLayer p/ gdistance

# Asegurar costos > 0; mantener NA como barreras
vals <- getValues(resistance_matrix)
eps <- 1e-6
vals[!is.na(vals) & vals <= 0] <- eps
resistance_matrix <- setValues(resistance_matrix, vals)

# --------------------------
# 1) Preparar parches (sf)
# --------------------------
# Asumo que ya tienes habitat_nodes leÃ­do como sf
# habitat_nodes <- read_sf("D:/TAYASSU/Shapes/tayassu parches.shp")

habitat_nodes$Id <- seq_len(nrow(habitat_nodes))
habitat_nodes <- st_make_valid(habitat_nodes)
habitat_nodes <- habitat_nodes[!st_is_empty(habitat_nodes), ]

# Proyectar a CRS del raster (en metros)
habitat_nodes <- st_transform(habitat_nodes, st_crs(resistance_matrix))

# Calcular Ã¡rea en mÂ² desde la geometrÃ­a
habitat_nodes <- habitat_nodes %>%
  mutate(area_m2 = as.numeric(st_area(geometry)))

# --------------------------
# 2) PRIORIZAR por Ã¡rea: Ã¡rea â¥ ÏÂ·rÂ²
# --------------------------
habitat_filtrados <- habitat_nodes %>%
  filter(area_m2 >= umbral_area_m2)

# (Opcional) tomar hasta N parches
N <- min(50, nrow(habitat_filtrados))
parches_ejemplo <- habitat_filtrados %>%
  slice_sample(n = N) %>%
  mutate(Id = row_number())

# --------------------------
# 3) Matriz de transiciÃ³n
# --------------------------
tr <- transition(resistance_matrix, function(x) 1 / mean(x), directions = 8)
tr <- geoCorrection(tr, type = "c")

# --------------------------
# 4) Centroides vÃ¡lidos
# --------------------------
sf_use_s2(FALSE)
## Spherical geometry (s2) switched off
centroides_sf <- st_point_on_surface(parches_ejemplo) %>%
  st_transform(st_crs(resistance_matrix))
## Warning: st_point_on_surface assumes attributes are constant over geometries
xy <- st_coordinates(centroides_sf)

# Quedarse con centroides sobre celdas vÃ¡lidas (no-NA y costo > 0)
cells <- cellFromXY(resistance_matrix, xy)
vals  <- resistance_matrix[][cells]
keep  <- !is.na(cells) & !is.na(vals) & is.finite(vals) & (vals > 0)

xy_valid  <- xy[keep, , drop = FALSE]
id_valid  <- parches_ejemplo$Id[keep]


# --------------------------
# 5) Rutas de menor costo
# --------------------------
rutas_template <- st_sf(
  geometry = st_sfc(crs = st_crs(habitat_nodes)),
  from = integer(),
  to   = integer()
)

safe_shortest_path <- function(tr, src, dst, from_id, to_id, crs_out) {
  sp <- tryCatch(
    shortestPath(tr, src, dst, output = "SpatialLines"),
    error = function(e) NULL
  )
  if (is.null(sp) || length(sp) == 0) return(NULL)

  sf_line <- tryCatch(st_as_sf(sp), error = function(e) NULL)
  if (is.null(sf_line) || nrow(sf_line) == 0) return(NULL)

  st_crs(sf_line) <- crs_out
  sf_line %>%
    dplyr::select(geometry) %>%
    mutate(from = as.integer(from_id),
           to   = as.integer(to_id))
}

rutas_list <- vector("list", nrow(xy_valid) - 1)
for (i in 1:(nrow(xy_valid) - 1)) {
  rutas_list[[i]] <- map_dfr((i + 1):nrow(xy_valid), function(j) {
    safe_shortest_path(tr, xy_valid[i, ], xy_valid[j, ],
                       from_id = id_valid[i], to_id = id_valid[j],
                       crs_out = st_crs(habitat_nodes))
  }, .id = NULL)
}

rutas_mc <- suppressWarnings({
  out <- dplyr::bind_rows(rutas_list)
  if (is.null(out) || nrow(out) == 0) rutas_template else out
})

message("Rutas vÃ¡lidas construidas: ", nrow(rutas_mc))
## Rutas vÃ¡lidas construidas: 10

#Delta de PC

#Distancia efectiva promedio como umbral de distancia
Effec_mean <- mean(resistance_matrix[], na.rm = TRUE) * 7106

#Aplicamos la funciÃ³n
delta <- MK_dPCIIC_links(nodes = parches_ejemplo,
                         attribute = NULL,
                         area_unit = "ha",
                         distance = list(type = "least-cost", 
                                         resistance = resistance_matrix),
                         removal = TRUE,
                         metric = "PC",
                         probability = 0.5,
                         distance_thresholds = round(Effec_mean),
                         parallel = NULL,
                         parallel_mode = 0,
                         intern = TRUE)
